Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a
large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large, preferably
ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.
Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp}.

Stir @marinara sauce{1%14oz cup}, @milk{6.75%ounce}, and @butter{1%tbsp} into pan.
Bring to a boil, then stir in as many @?chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like and
half the @spinach{5%ounce} (all the spinach for 4 servings). Cook, stirring,
until spinach wilts, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir drained penne into sauce. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Evenly sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}.
Top with a large drizzle of olive oil.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a baking dish.

Bake penne mixture until panko is browned and crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}. Divide
between plates and serve.